 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Test Analyst L2 Capgemini 8,255 reviews Milford, CT Capgemini 8,255 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Contract Full Job Description Duration :6+Months 
Responsibilities : 
Atleast 3-4 years of Web and Mobile app accessibility testing experience 
Must have in depth knowledge of accessibility related standards and guidelines 
Must have knowledge of ADA/508/WCAG2.0 compliance 
Thorough understanding of W3C standards-compliant HTML and CSS 
Must have experience in testing of Mobile applications and Android devices 
Should able to define accessibility test scenarios and test conditions 
Should develop detailed accessibility test plans 
Should have experience in working with Accessibility tools for major browsers - Firefox, IE, Chrome and Safari 
Should be familiar with accessibility implementation techniques like right use of ARIA attributes, logical order; correct semantics 
Knowledge of assistive technologies used for web browsing such as JAWS or NVDA 
Should have experience in using shortcuts and keystrokes for assistive technologies 
Excellent oral and written communication skills 
Requirements : 
Document internal processes for testing to ensure compliance with ADA standards 
Conduct in-depth compliance assessments via manual reviews 
Compile reports concerning failures in compliance and ways to remediate 
Review ADA compliance defects with developers and discuss possible resolutions 
Provide expert advice to other teams testing web pages and applications for ADA compliance 
Assist project teams with understanding how accessibility activities fit within the project life cycle 
Partner with project leads and requirements analysts to help them appropriately document and deliver against requirements for ADA compliance 
Stay up-to-date on the latest regulations and automated tool information 
